reviewText: great movie:)
I freaking love this movie "That Thing You Do". I watched "once" for a few minutes. They say the f word a lot and It was difficult to find the relevance of this movie.
My son is a young drummer, so my wife and I wanted to share this movie with him. I didn't realize how many catch phrases I say to my kids that came from this movie.
I love "That Thing You Do".  I love watching it with my wife.  It is a fun, feel good move!  I have not yet watched "Once".
The movie was great but for being a new and unused dvd. There was a scratch when i first open it. And has a skip in one part of the movie. Great deal for dvds.

I really like That Thing You do.  I remember seeing it a a child and I really liked it then.  I am into music myself and It was a good movie about what can happen with a band that is just trying to make a name for themselves.
Once is not such a good movie It uses a lot of bad language right from the start.  I do not like that kind of movie and was not pleased with it when I bought it.

I ordered this pack for That Thing You Do (I have never seen or heard of Once), which is a great movie. Written, directed, and featuring Tom Hanks. This movie follows the tale of a band in the early 1960's and their journey to fame. Humorous, a little dramatic, and fun as heck. I would definitely recommend this movie.
It is so nice these days to find a movie you can sit back and enjoy with the family without all the hyper cyber visual effects. No dramatics just development of characters as a good movie should be.
So many junk movies come out that when I find a good quality movie, I buy it to watch again. Good script, good actors, good acting, good music!

This product didn't work. After it was received as the gift I inteneded to cheer someone up, and it didn't work, I found out that it was made for use in the UK. Don't you think that would have been a good thing to say on the websight for customers to know before ordering it?
MY FAVORITE MOVIE!!!  Thanks!

I do not understand the pairing of "Once" with "That Thing You Do." I started watching "Once" and turned it off after a few minutes; it was terrible. The only reason I purchased it was "That Thing You Do" by itself cost so much more than this combo "deal."
